ram\": \"The group\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"the attack\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2137}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regular readers may remember the name in connection with theattack on an Indonesian national datacentera few months ago, which affected more than 200 government institutions.\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2245, \"end\": 2255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\", \"score\": 0.9529439443620035, \"rank\": 0.04723044669329641, \"text\": \"Indonesian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Regular readers\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"connection\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"theattack\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 200 government institutions\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cybersecurity researchers believe Brain Cipher developed its ransomware payload based on theLockBit3.0 builder, which was leaked in 2022.\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cybersecurity researchers\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"Brain Cipher\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"its ransomware payload\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2427}, {\"ngram\": \"theLockBit3.0 builder\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many fledgling groups have done the same, so there is nothing to suggest the two groups are linked in any way, other than their penchant for digital mischief.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2644, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many fledgling groups\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2507}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"the two groups\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2573}, {\"ngram\": \"any way\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2595}, {\"ngram\": \"their penchant\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2622}, {\"ngram\": \"digital mischief\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The leaked builder gives baby ransomware gangs a leg up in terms of being able to start attacking organizations with little setup and development time, but comes with a major drawback.\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2830, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The leaked builder\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2664}, {\"ngram\": \"baby ransomware\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2686}, {\"ngram\": \"a leg\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"organizations\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"little setup\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2775}, {\"ngram\": \"development time\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2796}, {\"ngram\": \"a major drawback\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2829}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its signatures are widely known, meaning those with robust, regularly updated defenses will likely be able to detect and quarantine an attack before any real nastiness can unfold.\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its signatures\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2845}, {\"ngram\": \"robust, regularly updated defenses\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2917}, {\"ngram\": \"an attack\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"any real nastiness\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 2998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, SentinelOne and SOCRadar both said in their respective rundowns of Brain Cipher that its payload appears to feature more advanced code obfuscation techniques than the leaked LockBit builder, making analysis of how it works more difficult.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3021, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SentinelOne\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SentinelOne\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SentinelOne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SentinelOne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"SOCRadar\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3045}, {\"ngram\": \"their respective rundowns\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3084}, {\"ngram\": \"Brain Cipher\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3100}, {\"ngram\": \"its payload\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3117}, {\"ngram\": \"more advanced code obfuscation techniques\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3178}, {\"ngram\": \"the leaked LockBit builder\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3210}, {\"ngram\": \"analysis\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Brain Cipher is equipped with several persistence and evasion techniques,\\\"saidSOCRadar.\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3349, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brain Cipher\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3274}, {\"ngram\": \"several persistence\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3311}, {\"ngram\": \"evasion techniques,\\\"saidSOCRadar\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It hides threads from debuggers and executes in a suspended mode to avoid detection.\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"threads\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3367}, {\"ngram\": \"debuggers\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"executes\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3395}, {\"ngram\": \"a suspended mode\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3415}, {\"ngram\": \"detection\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, it enables debug and security privileges, potentially allowing it to bypass security measures.\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"debug\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3466}, {\"ngram\": \"security privileges\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3490}, {\"ngram\": \"security measures\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3543}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The use of code obfuscation further complicates detection and analysis efforts.\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3624, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The use\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3552}, {\"ngram\": \"code obfuscation\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3572}, {\"ngram\": \"detection and analysis efforts\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The obfuscation technique used in Brain Cipher involves the instruction sequence push FFFFFF9Ch; retf.\", \"from\": 3626, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The obfuscation technique\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3652}, {\"ngram\": \"Brain Cipher\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"the instruction sequence\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3707}, {\"ngram\": \"FFFFFF9Ch\", \"from\": 3713, \"to\": 3722}, {\"ngram\": \"retf\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This sequence pushes the hexadecimal value FFFFFF9C onto the stack and then performs a far return (retf), which uses the value on the stack to alter the instruction pointer and code segment registers.\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3930, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This sequence\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"the hexadecimal value\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3772}, {\"ngram\": \"the stack\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3796}, {\"ngram\": \"a far return\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3827}, {\"ngram\": \"retf\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3833}, {\"ngram\": \"the value\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3856}, {\"ngram\": \"the stack\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 3869}, {\"ngram\": \"the instruction pointer and code segment registers\", \"from\": 3879, \"to\": 3929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This method complicates the control flow, making it difficult for analysis tools and researchers to trace the malware's execution path.\\\"\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 4067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This method\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 3942}, {\"ngram\": \"the control flow\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 3971}, {\"ngram\": \"analysis tools\", \"from